author: Mohammed Jeeshan Sheikh

text:
Some things are better written than told, that's why I wanted you create an account.

Confessing that I pictured you completely wrong. A guy who keeps smiling all the time, places some family photos in his shelves, plugs in earphones in lecture halls and prefers watching House at night over the 'Taua' assignment next day.ğŸ™ğŸ» 
I think I've seen you sleep at every place we have been to in campus!
But with time I realized that's a choice you have made for yourself, not giving attention to things more than they deserve.
I personally admire that you don't budge easily, when everyone else is going mainstream. (But I'll keep pushing you about certain things you claim lack credibility ; your parents naming you 'Dev' is perhaps the biggest irony of your life ğŸ˜œ)
Sharma referred to us as the 'chemical bros of E-bot' in my memoir which I found funny given the differences we carry about a *LOT* of stuff, but that's amazing how we have gelled given that too.
(Chapai mein hum log pakde nhi gaye kabhi, that's a relief!)

Anyways, there are a dozen things which I need to thank you for, taking care of me at my worst is just one of them. â£ï¸
Thanks mate for being the sweetest spoken person I met, 'listening' to stuff I say and sharing this walk of life alongside.
Stay in touch ğŸ––
